<% details = legal_details(region) %>
<% config = RegionHelper.region_config(region) %>

<div class="legal-document">
  <div class="legal-header">
    <h1>Wholesale Funding Agreement</h1>
    <p class="legal-jurisdiction"><%= config["name"] %> — <%= config["code"] %></p>
    <p class="legal-version">Version <%= legal_version %> | Effective: <%= legal_date %></p>
    <p class="legal-regulated">Regulated by: <%= details[:regulator] %></p>
  </div>

  <div class="legal-body">
    <h2>1. PARTIES</h2>
    <p><strong>1.1 The Wholesale Funder:</strong> [Funder Name], (<%= details[:company_registration] %>: [Number]), of [Registered Address] (the "<strong>Funder</strong>").</p>
    <p><strong>1.2 The Lender:</strong> [Lender Name], licensed under <%= details[:licensing_act] %>, of [Registered Address] (the "<strong>Lender</strong>").</p>
    <p><strong>1.3 The Platform:</strong> FutureProof Financial, operating the FutureProof EPM Platform (the "<strong>Platform</strong>").</p>

    <h2>2. PURPOSE</h2>
    <p><strong>2.1</strong> The Funder agrees to provide wholesale capital to the Lender for the purpose of funding Equity Preservation Mortgages (EPMs) originated through the Platform.</p>
    <p><strong>2.2</strong> The Funder's capital shall be deployed exclusively for EPM products and not for any other lending purpose.</p>

    <h2>3. CAPITAL COMMITMENT</h2>
    <p><strong>3.1</strong> The Funder commits to provide up to <%= config["currency_symbol"] %>[Amount] in wholesale funding (the "<strong>Facility Limit</strong>").</p>
    <p><strong>3.2</strong> Drawdowns shall be made in accordance with the Drawdown Schedule annexed hereto.</p>
    <p><strong>3.3</strong> The Funder may increase or decrease the Facility Limit upon [30] days' written notice.</p>

    <h2>4. RETURNS AND FEES</h2>
    <p><strong>4.1</strong> The Funder shall receive a wholesale margin of [X]% per annum on deployed capital.</p>
    <p><strong>4.2</strong> Returns shall be calculated quarterly and paid within [15] business days of the quarter end.</p>
    <p><strong>4.3</strong> The Funder shall have visibility of performance metrics through the Platform's Wholesale Funder Portal.</p>

    <h2>5. REPORTING</h2>
    <p><strong>5.1</strong> The Platform shall provide the Funder with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>(a) Monthly portfolio performance reports;</li>
      <li>(b) Quarterly detailed financial statements;</li>
      <li>(c) Annual audited accounts;</li>
      <li>(d) Real-time dashboard access via the Platform.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>5.2</strong> Reports shall include: total capital deployed, allocation by lender, return on deployed capital (XIRR, CAGR), portfolio health indicators, loan performance, risk exposure, and available capacity.</p>

    <h2>6. RISK MANAGEMENT</h2>
    <p><strong>6.1</strong> The Platform maintains a Pool Coverage mechanism to manage investment shortfall risk.</p>
    <p><strong>6.2</strong> Lenders Mortgage Insurance (LMI) is obtained on all EPM loans at 2% of loan amount.</p>
    <p><strong>6.3</strong> Maximum LTV ratio is capped at <%= (config["max_ltv"].to_f * 100).to_i %>% across all loans.</p>

    <h2>7. COMPLIANCE</h2>
    <p><strong>7.1</strong> All parties comply with applicable requirements under <%= details[:consumer_credit_act] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>7.2</strong> Anti-money laundering obligations under <%= details[:aml_act] %> are strictly observed.</p>
    <p><strong>7.3</strong> The Funder's data is protected under <%= details[:privacy_act] %>.</p>

    <h2>8. TERMINATION</h2>
    <p><strong>8.1</strong> Either party may terminate this Agreement upon [90] days' written notice.</p>
    <p><strong>8.2</strong> Upon termination, existing funded loans shall continue to maturity under the terms of this Agreement.</p>

    <h2>9. DISPUTE RESOLUTION</h2>
    <p><strong>9.1</strong> Disputes shall be resolved through <%= details[:dispute_resolution] %>.</p>

    <h2>10. GOVERNING LAW</h2>
    <p><strong>10.1</strong> This Agreement is governed by <%= details[:governing_law] %>.</p>
    <p><strong>10.2</strong> The parties submit to the jurisdiction of <%= details[:courts] %>.</p>

    <div class="legal-signatures">
      <div class="legal-signature-block">
        <p><strong>SIGNED by the WHOLESALE FUNDER:</strong></p>
        <p>Name: ___________________________ Title: ___________________________</p>
        <p>Signature: ___________________________ Date: ___________________________</p>
      </div>
      <div class="legal-signature-block">
        <p><strong>SIGNED by the LENDER:</strong></p>
        <p>Name: ___________________________ Title: ___________________________</p>
        <p>Signature: ___________________________ Date: ___________________________</p>
      </div>
      <div class="legal-signature-block">
        <p><strong>SIGNED by the PLATFORM:</strong></p>
        <p>Name: ___________________________ Title: ___________________________</p>
        <p>Signature: ___________________________ Date: ___________________________</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
